description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Diagnostic Radiographer within the busy radiology department at Colchester General Hospital. Must have 18 months post qualifications experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is a Full time position - 37.5 Hours Per Week. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Come join our fabulous Diagnostic Radiography team at Colchester Hospital. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our team is very friendly and helpful, and we are committed to providing a top standard medical imaging experience. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be a confident and enthusiastic individual who is proficient in all aspects of radiology and CT scanning. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have over 180 years of collective clinical experience between us &amp; are a very generous team regarding both teaching and other role elements. We are a supportive and can do team, and are looking for an individual with the same motivation and positive attitude we currently excel. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role May required you to travel to other service providers as and when to suit departmental needs. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Diagnostic services are located across Colchester Hospital, The Primary Care Trust, Clacton Hospital, Harwich and Halstead Hospitals/ healthcare centres. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is 24 hours, 365 days per annum. The requirement is to work a rostered week over 7 days. Participating in 18 week shift pattern, to cover nights and weekends and to cover trauma and urgent ward patients.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have the opportunity to work alongside highly skilled and experienced colleagues and become involved in our dedication to provide a good service for patients.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details or an informal chat on what you may be looking for, please contact me directly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
